==English==

===Etymology===
From "Turkey traders", who imported  [[guinea fowl]] into Europe in the 16th century. ''[[Melaegris ocellata]]'' were thought to resemble guinea fowl.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈtɜː.kɪ/}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|tûr'kē}}, {{IPA|/ˈtɝː.kɪ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-turkey.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɜː(r)ki}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Either of two species of [[bird]] in the genus ''[[Meleagris]]'' with fan-shaped [[tail]]s and [[wattle]]d [[neck]]s.
# {{colloquial}} A [[failure]].
#: ''That film was a '''turkey'''.''
# {{slang|usually|mildly|derogatory}} A [[foolish]] or [[inept]] person.
#: ''The '''turkey''' cut in front of me and then berated me for running into him.''
# {{bowling}} The act of throwing three [[strike]]s in a row.

